x4freetext: TUNL FN Tandem Van de Graaff and Mini-
The outgoing alpha-particles were detected by
eight silicon surface barrier detectors with
sufficient thickness to stop the alpha-particles at
microg/cm2 of isotopically pure 11B deposited on a 9
microg/cm2 carbon backing. Target thickness was
at 4.86 MeV, where the ratio of the elastic
scattering cross section to the purely
electromagnetic Rutherford cross section is known.
Analyses of elastic scattering and energy loss agree
and provide a target thickness of 56+-2 microg/cm2
leading to a 3.6% systematic uncertainty in our yields.
Approved by Mark Sikora on March 22, 2024.
